> Look into Flutter [ImageCache](https://api.flutter.dev/flutter/painting/ImageCache/ImageCache.html) class, it is exposed globally via `imageCache`
> 
> In my case I just told image cache that I did not want to cache any image (just to test if it fixed the issue), you should cache only stuff you need to cache.

Some like this?

class MyImageCache extends ImageCache {
  @override
  void clear() {
    print("Clearing cache!");
    super.clear();
  }
}
class MyWidgetsBinding extends WidgetsFlutterBinding {
  @override
  ImageCache createImageCache() {
    MyImageCache myImageCache = MyImageCache();
    myImageCache.maximumSize = 0;
    return myImageCache;
  }
}

void main() {
  runApp(MyApp());
  MyWidgetsBinding();

}

